{
  "text": "Microemboli are markers of disease activity, not the disease itself. Microemboli have been associated with carotid plaque inflammation [CITATION_1] , coagulopathies [CITATION_2] ) and platelet activation markers [CITATION_3] ). Adding information on basic disease mechanisms may improve our understanding of the complex pathophysiology of acute embolic stroke as defined by MES monitoring.",
